other_tests.findings: Germline p53 gene mutation detected in exon 10, codon 336 (E336X). Another mutation occurred in the granulosa cell tumor in exon 7.
Multifocal granulosa cell tumor with atypical TP53 positive nuclei, hyperchromatism, abundant mitoses, and numerous hyaline globules.
7 cm multicystic mass in the right ovary, which was treated by salpingo-oophorectomy.
other_tests.changes_over_time: The contralateral ovary was normal in appearance.

other_tests.findings: Suspicious uterine fundal masses revealed intramural leiomyomas and an incipient endometrioid adenocarcinoma.
